27using ParamData = std::vector<std::vector<uint8_t>>;
28struct ParamCapture : angle::NonCopyable
29{
30 ParamCapture();
31 ParamCapture(const char *nameIn, ParamType typeIn);
32 ~ParamCapture();
33
34 ParamCapture(ParamCapture &&other);
35 ParamCapture &operator=(ParamCapture &&other);
36
37 std::string name;
38 ParamType type;
39 ParamValue value;
40 gl::GLenumGroup enumGroup; // only used for param type GLenum, GLboolean and GLbitfield
41 ParamData data;
42 int arrayClientPointerIndex = -1;
43 size_t readBufferSizeBytes = 0;
44};

58 void addEnumParam(const char *paramName,
59 gl::GLenumGroup enumGroup,
60 ParamType paramType,
61 T paramValue);
62
63 ParamCapture &getParam(const char *paramName, ParamType paramType, int index);
64 const ParamCapture &getParam(const char *paramName, ParamType paramType, int index) const;
65 ParamCapture &getParamFlexName(const char *paramName1,
66 const char *paramName2,
67 ParamType paramType,
68 int index);
69 const ParamCapture &getParamFlexName(const char *paramName1,
70 const char *paramName2,
71 ParamType paramType,
72 int index) const;
73 const ParamCapture &getReturnValue() const { return mReturnValueCapture; }
74
75 void addParam(ParamCapture &&param);
76 void addReturnValue(ParamCapture &&returnValue);
77 bool hasClientArrayData() const { return mClientArrayDataParam != -1; }
78 ParamCapture &getClientArrayPointerParameter();

80
81 const std::vector<ParamCapture> &getParamCaptures() const { return mParamCaptures; }
82
83 // These helpers allow us to track the ID of the buffer that was active when

113class ReplayContext
114{
115 public:
116 ReplayContext(size_t readBufferSizebytes, const gl::AttribArray<size_t> &clientArraysSizebytes);
117 ~ReplayContext();
118
119 template <typename T>
120 T getReadBufferPointer(const ParamCapture &param)
121 {
122 ASSERT(param.readBufferSizeBytes > 0);
123 ASSERT(mReadBuffer.size() >= param.readBufferSizeBytes);
124 return reinterpret_cast<T>(mReadBuffer.data());
125 }
126 template <typename T>
127 T getAsConstPointer(const ParamCapture &param)
128 {
129 if (param.arrayClientPointerIndex != -1)
130 {
131 return reinterpret_cast<T>(mClientArraysBuffer[param.arrayClientPointerIndex].data());
132 }
133
134 if (!param.data.empty())
135 {
136 ASSERT(param.data.size() == 1);
137 return reinterpret_cast<T>(param.data[0].data());
138 }
139
140 return nullptr;
141 }
142
143 template <typename T>
144 T getAsPointerConstPointer(const ParamCapture &param)
145 {
146 static_assert(sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type) == sizeof(uint8_t *),
147 "pointer size not match!");
148
149 ASSERT(!param.data.empty());
150 mPointersBuffer.clear();
151 mPointersBuffer.reserve(param.data.size());
152 for (const std::vector<uint8_t> &data : param.data)
153 {
154 mPointersBuffer.emplace_back(data.data());
155 }
156 return reinterpret_cast<T>(mPointersBuffer.data());
157 }
158
159 gl::AttribArray<std::vector<uint8_t>> &getClientArraysBuffer() { return mClientArraysBuffer; }
160
161 private:
162 std::vector<uint8_t> mReadBuffer;
163 std::vector<const uint8_t *> mPointersBuffer;
164 gl::AttribArray<std::vector<uint8_t>> mClientArraysBuffer;
165};

210using BufferSet = std::set<gl::BufferID>;
211using BufferCalls = std::map<gl::BufferID, std::vector<CallCapture>>;
212
213// true means mapped, false means unmapped
214using BufferMapStatusMap = std::map<gl::BufferID, bool>;

216// Helper to track resource changes during the capture
217class ResourceTracker final : angle::NonCopyable
218{
219 public:
220 ResourceTracker();
221 ~ResourceTracker();
222
223 BufferCalls &getBufferRegenCalls() { return mBufferRegenCalls; }
224 BufferCalls &getBufferRestoreCalls() { return mBufferRestoreCalls; }
225 BufferCalls &getBufferMapCalls() { return mBufferMapCalls; }
226 BufferCalls &getBufferUnmapCalls() { return mBufferUnmapCalls; }
227
228 std::vector<CallCapture> &getBufferBindingCalls() { return mBufferBindingCalls; }
229
230 BufferSet &getStartingBuffers() { return mStartingBuffers; }
231 BufferSet &getNewBuffers() { return mNewBuffers; }
232 BufferSet &getBuffersToRegen() { return mBuffersToRegen; }
233 BufferSet &getBuffersToRestore() { return mBuffersToRestore; }
234
235 void setGennedBuffer(gl::BufferID id);
236 void setDeletedBuffer(gl::BufferID id);
237 void setBufferModified(gl::BufferID id);
238 void setBufferMapped(gl::BufferID id);
239 void setBufferUnmapped(gl::BufferID id);
240
241 const bool &getStartingBuffersMappedCurrent(gl::BufferID id)
242 {
243 return mStartingBuffersMappedCurrent[id];
244 }
245 const bool &getStartingBuffersMappedInitial(gl::BufferID id)
246 {
247 return mStartingBuffersMappedInitial[id];
248 }
249 void setStartingBufferMapped(gl::BufferID id, bool mapped)
250 {
251 // Track the current state (which will change throughout the trace)
252 mStartingBuffersMappedCurrent[id] = mapped;
253
254 // And the initial state, to compare during frame loop reset
255 mStartingBuffersMappedInitial[id] = mapped;
256 }
257
258 void onShaderProgramAccess(gl::ShaderProgramID shaderProgramID);
259 uint32_t getMaxShaderPrograms() const { return mMaxShaderPrograms; }
260
261 private:
262 // Buffer regen calls will delete and gen a buffer
263 BufferCalls mBufferRegenCalls;
264 // Buffer restore calls will restore the contents of a buffer
265 BufferCalls mBufferRestoreCalls;
266 // Buffer map calls will map a buffer with correct offset, length, and access flags
267 BufferCalls mBufferMapCalls;
268 // Buffer unmap calls will bind and unmap a given buffer
269 BufferCalls mBufferUnmapCalls;
270
271 // Buffer binding calls to restore bindings recorded during MEC
272 std::vector<CallCapture> mBufferBindingCalls;
273
274 // Starting buffers include all the buffers created during setup for MEC
275 BufferSet mStartingBuffers;
276 // New buffers are those generated while capturing
277 BufferSet mNewBuffers;
278 // Buffers to regen are a list of starting buffers that need to be deleted and genned
279 BufferSet mBuffersToRegen;
280 // Buffers to restore include any starting buffers with contents modified during the run
281 BufferSet mBuffersToRestore;
282
283 // Whether a given buffer was mapped at the start of the trace
284 BufferMapStatusMap mStartingBuffersMappedInitial;
285 // The status of buffer mapping throughout the trace, modified with each Map/Unmap call
286 BufferMapStatusMap mStartingBuffersMappedCurrent;
287
288 // Maximum accessed shader program ID.
289 uint32_t mMaxShaderPrograms = 0;
290};

423template <typename CaptureFuncT, typename... ArgsT>
424void CaptureCallToFrameCapture(CaptureFuncT captureFunc,
425 bool isCallValid,
426 gl::Context *context,
427 ArgsT... captureParams)
428{
429 FrameCapture *frameCapture = context->getFrameCapture();
430 if (!frameCapture->isCapturing())
431 return;
432
433 CallCapture call = captureFunc(context->getState(), isCallValid, captureParams...);
434
435 if (!isCallValid)
436 INFO() << "FrameCapture: Capturing invalid call to " << GetEntryPointName(call.entryPoint);
437
438 frameCapture->captureCall(context, std::move(call));
439}

441template <typename T>
442void ParamBuffer::addValueParam(const char *paramName, ParamType paramType, T paramValue)
443{
444 ParamCapture capture(paramName, paramType);
445 InitParamValue(paramType, paramValue, &capture.value);
446 mParamCaptures.emplace_back(std::move(capture));
447}
448
449template <typename T>
450void ParamBuffer::addEnumParam(const char *paramName,
451 gl::GLenumGroup enumGroup,
452 ParamType paramType,
453 T paramValue)
454{
455 ParamCapture capture(paramName, paramType);
456 InitParamValue(paramType, paramValue, &capture.value);
457 capture.enumGroup = enumGroup;
458 mParamCaptures.emplace_back(std::move(capture));
459}

482template <typename T>
483void CaptureClearBufferValue(GLenum buffer, const T *value, ParamCapture *paramCapture)
484{
485 // Per the spec, color buffers have a vec4, the rest a single value
486 uint32_t valueSize = (buffer == GL_COLOR) ? 4 : 1;
487 CaptureMemory(value, valueSize * sizeof(T), paramCapture);
488}

492template <typename T>
493void CaptureGenHandles(GLsizei n, T *handles, ParamCapture *paramCapture)

604template <typename T>
605void CaptureTextureAndSamplerParameter_params(GLenum pname,
606 const T *param,
607 angle::ParamCapture *paramCapture)
608{
609 if (pname == GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR)
610 {
611 CaptureMemory(param, sizeof(T) * 4, paramCapture);
612 }
613 else
614 {
615 CaptureMemory(param, sizeof(T), paramCapture);
616 }
